This program will search for every instance of a substring in a larger text.
Usage: substring <query string>
The text should be provided from standard in
 Example:
    $echo mississippi | substring ssi 
to search for all instances of 'ssi' in 'mississippi'

I have also included a version of the mycobacterium tuberculosis genome with 
the comments, whitespace, numbers, and line breaks stripped out for use by 
this program ("Mtuberculosis.txt")

To find all instances of "tggccggtgc" in Mycobacterium tuberculosis genome:

    $substring tggccggtgc < Mtuberculosis.txt 
